entity.name: Rebecca Welton
entity.text:
Rebecca Welton is a bold leader who has transformed the club from a struggling team to a winning one, with the help of Ted Lasso and her team. She overcomes personal and professional challenges including crippling self-doubt with grace and courage, and inspires many people along the way including helping another female leader (Keely) by encouraging her and always having her back. Never talking down to her! Her empathy is just... [...] Hey, Ted Lasso fans! Do you agree with me that Rebecca Welton is the real star of the show? She is the CEO of AFC Richmond and one of the most badass female leaders I've seen on TV. Here are some of the reasons why I think she possess transformational leadership qualities.

 🎆She supports Ted and his unconventional methods and trusts him to do his job.

🎆She empowers her team to perform their best and gives them autonomy and responsibility. [...] What I find most amazing about Rebecca Welton is that she leads her team to victory even though she is uncomfortable and knows little about managing a football team. She does this by bringing the team together and trusting her leadership team. This shows that she is a transformational leader who can create a positive change in her organization.
